A diall, wherein is contained a remembrance of death, and the uncertainty of the time of death. With many good rules how for to lead a good life. Granger, William.
[16] p.
[s.n.], London : printed, anno, 1648.
In verse. "To the reader" signed: William Granger. Signatures: A-B⁴. With a title-page woodcut. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Feb. 27"; the 8 in imprint date crossed out and date altered to 1647. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
